{"title":"Shimea","link":"/en/wol/d/r1/lp-e/1200004042","html":"<span id=\"page930\" class=\"pageNum\" data-no=\"930\" data-before-text=\"930\"></span><strong>SHIMEA</strong>(Shim&#x2B9;e&#xB7;a) [possibly a shortened form of Shemaiah, meaning &#x201C;Jehovah Has Heard (Listened)&#x201D;].<strong>1. </strong>A Merarite Levite.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/0/0\" data-bid=\"1-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 6:29,&#xA0;30</a>.<strong>2. </strong>Ancestor of temple musician Asaph in the Levitical family of Gershon (Gershom).<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/1/0\" data-bid=\"2-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 6:1,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/1/1\" data-bid=\"2-2\" class=\"b\"> 39,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/1/2\" data-bid=\"2-3\" class=\"b\"> 43;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/1/3\" data-bid=\"2-4\" class=\"b\"> Ex 6:16</a>.<strong>3. </strong>The third son of Jesse, hence an older brother of David.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/2/0\" data-bid=\"3-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 2:13,</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/2/1\" data-bid=\"3-2\" class=\"b\"> 15;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/2/2\" data-bid=\"3-3\" class=\"b\"> 20:7</a>; see <a class=\"it\" href=\"/en/wol/tc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/0\">SHAMMAH</a> No.&#xA0;2.<strong>4. </strong>A son borne by Bath-sheba to David. (<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/3/0\" data-bid=\"4-1\" class=\"b\">1Ch 3:5</a>) He is elsewhere called Shammua.<wbr>&#x2014;<a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/4/0\" data-bid=\"5-1\" class=\"b\">2Sa 5:14;</a><a href=\"/en/wol/bc/r1/lp-e/1200004042/4/1\" data-bid=\"5-2\" class=\"b\"> 1Ch 14:4</a>."}